{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.36",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 36 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:1",
      "text": "And Elius further continued, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:2",
      "text": "Wait for me yet a little while, that I may teach thee: for there is yet speech in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:3",
      "text": "Having fetched my knowledge from afar, and according to my works,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:4",
      "text": "I will speak just things truly, and thou shalt not unjustly receive unjust words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:5",
      "text": "But know that the Lord will not cast off an innocent man: being mighty in strength of wisdom,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:6",
      "text": "he will not by any means save alive the ungodly: and he will grant the judgment of the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:7",
      "text": "He will not turn away his eyes from the righteous, but they shall be with kings on the throne: and he will establish them in triumph, and they shall be exalted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:8",
      "text": "But they that are bound in fetters shall be holden in cords of poverty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:9",
      "text": "And he shall recount to them their works, and their transgressions, for such will act with violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:10",
      "text": "But he will hearken to the righteous: and he has said that they shall turn from unrighteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:11",
      "text": "If they should hear and serve him, they shall spend their days in prosperity, and their years in honour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:12",
      "text": "But he preserves not the ungodly; because they are not willing to know the Lord, and because when reproved they were disobedient.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:13",
      "text": "And the hypocrites in heart will array wrath against themselves; they will not cry, because he has bound them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:14",
      "text": "Therefore let their soul die in youth, and their life be wounded by messengers of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:15",
      "text": "Because they afflicted the weak and helpless: and he will vindicate the judgment of the meek.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:16",
      "text": "And he has also enticed thee out of the mouth of the enemy:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:17",
      "text": "there is a deep gulf and a rushing stream beneath it, and thy table came down full of fatness. Judgment shall not fail from the righteous;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:18",
      "text": "but there shall be wrath upon the ungodly, by reason of the ungodliness of the bribes which they received for iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:19",
      "text": "Let not thy mind willingly turn thee aside from the petition of the feeble that are in distress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:20",
      "text": "And draw not forth all the mighty men by night, so that the people should go up instead of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:21",
      "text": "But take heed lest thou do that which is wrong: for of this thou hast made choice because of poverty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:22",
      "text": "Behold, the Mighty One shall prevail by his strength: for who is powerful as he is?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:23",
      "text": "And who is he that examines his works? or who can say, He has wrought injustice?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:24",
      "text": "Remember that his works are great beyond those which men have attempted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:25",
      "text": "Every man has seen in himself, how many mortals are wounded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:26",
      "text": "Behold, the Mighty One is great, and we shall not know him: the number of his years is even infinite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:27",
      "text": "And the drops of rain are numbered by him, and shall be poured out in rain to form a cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:28",
      "text": "The ancient heavens shall flow, and the clouds overshadow innumerable mortals: 28a he has fixed a time to cattle, and they know the order of rest. 28b Yet by all these things thy understanding is not astonished, neither is thy mind disturbed in thy body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:29",
      "text": "And though one should understand the outspreadings of the clouds, or the measure of his tabernacle;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:30",
      "text": "behold he will stretch his bow against him, and he covers the bottom of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:31",
      "text": "For by them he will judge the nations: he will give food to him that has strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:32",
      "text": "He has hidden the light in his hands, and given charge concerning it to the interposing cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.36.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:33",
      "text": "The Lord will declare concerning this to his friend: but there is a portion also for unrighteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
